{"BR": {"BR_id": "900", "BR_author": "patryk-s", "BRopenT": "2020-07-09T15:28:41Z", "BRcloseT": "2020-07-09T17:07:25Z", "BR_text": {"BRsummary": "Changing default namespace in helm chart doesn't effect polyaxon-operator -- jobs stuck in queue", "BRdescription": "\n <denchmark-h:h3>Describe the bug</denchmark-h>\n \n Deploying to a different namespace than polyaxon leaves all experiments in queued state.\n After some time, I figured out that the polyaxon-operator's --namespace config option is not set, and it doesn't use the POLYAXON_K8S_NAMESPACE env from polyaxon-config configMap (I guess it's expecting NAMESPACE)\n <denchmark-h:h3>To Reproduce</denchmark-h>\n \n helm install polyaxon polyaxon/polyaxon --namespace=polyaxon1 -f config.yaml\n polyaxon project create --name=quick-start --description='Polyaxon quick start.'\n polyaxon run --url=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/polyaxon/polyaxon-quick-start/master/experimentation/simple.yml\n NOTE: I have namespace: polyaxon1 in config.yaml\n <denchmark-h:h3>Expected behavior</denchmark-h>\n \n Experiment starts.\n <denchmark-h:h3>Environment</denchmark-h>\n \n Kubernetes\n \t"}, "comments": {"comments_0": {"comment_id": 1, "comment_author": "patryk-s", "commentT": "2020-07-09T17:09:38Z", "comment_text": "\n \t\tA new release v1.1.3 for Polyaxon CE will be made in the next few minutes including a patch for this. Thanks for reporting.\n \t\t"}}}, "commit": {"commit_id": "3e835111b6232aadc0fd098415ca4e84d09a63ee", "commit_author": "mouradmourafiq", "commitT": "2020-07-09 19:12:42+02:00", "changed_files": {"file_0": {"file_change_type": "MODIFY", "file_Nmethod": 0, "file_old_name": "README.md", "file_new_name": "README.md", "hunks": {"hunk_0": {"Ismethod": 0, "added_lines": "4", "deleted_lines": "4"}}}, "file_1": {"file_change_type": "MODIFY", "file_Nmethod": 0, "file_old_name": "charts\\agent\\Chart.yaml", "file_new_name": "charts\\agent\\Chart.yaml", "hunks": {"hunk_0": {"Ismethod": 0, "added_lines": "4,5", "deleted_lin